SIMPLE: encumbrance
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Encumbrance
<hw>En*cum"brance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>encombrance</ets>. Cf. <er>Incumbrance</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>That which encumbers; a burden which impedes action, or renders it
difficult and laborious; a clog; an impediment. See
<er>Incumbrance</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Same as
<er>Incumbrance</er>.</def></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Burden; clog; impediment; check;
hindrance.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encumbrancer</ent>⟦br⟧
